<%# SEO meta tags %>
<% set_meta_tags(
  title: "Character Counter - Free Online Tool",
  description: "Count characters, letters, digits, special characters, lines, and words in any text. Get detailed character analysis with this free online character counter.",
  canonical: everyday_character_counter_url,
  og: {
    title: "Character Counter - Free Online Tool | CalcWise",
    description: "Detailed character analysis: letters, digits, special characters, lines, and words. All counted instantly as you type.",
    url: everyday_character_counter_url,
    type: "website",
    site_name: "CalcWise"
  }
) %>

<%# JSON-LD schemas %>
<%= breadcrumb_schema([
  { name: "Home", url: root_url },
  { name: "Everyday", url: category_url("everyday") },
  { name: "Character Counter", url: everyday_character_counter_url }
]) %>

<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What is the difference between characters with and without spaces?", answer: "Characters with spaces counts every single character in your text including spaces, tabs, and newlines. Characters without spaces excludes all whitespace characters. This distinction matters for platforms with strict character limits. For example, some translation services charge per character excluding spaces, while others count everything." },
  { question: "What counts as a special character?", answer: "Special characters are any characters that are not letters, digits, or whitespace. This includes punctuation marks like periods, commas, and exclamation points, as well as symbols like @, #, $, %, and &. Brackets, quotes, and mathematical operators are also counted as special characters." },
  { question: "Why does my character count differ from Microsoft Word?", answer: "Different tools may handle whitespace differently. Some count only spaces, while others include tabs and newlines. Line endings can also vary: Windows uses two characters (CR+LF) per line break, while Mac and Linux use one (LF). Our counter counts each individual character exactly as it appears in the input." },
  { question: "What is a good character count for SEO meta descriptions?", answer: "Google typically displays 155-160 characters for meta descriptions on desktop and about 120 characters on mobile. Keeping your meta description under 155 characters ensures the full text is visible in search results. Title tags should be under 60 characters. Use this character counter to check your SEO text lengths." },
  { question: "Does the character counter support Unicode?", answer: "Yes, the character counter fully supports Unicode characters including accented letters, emoji, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Arabic, and Cyrillic characters. Each Unicode character is counted as one character regardless of how many bytes it uses in encoding." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema(
  name: "Character Counter",
  description: "Count characters, letters, digits, special characters, lines, and words in any text.",
  url: everyday_character_counter_url,
  category: "UtilityApplication"
) %>

<%# Breadcrumbs %>
<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", items: [
  { name: "Home", url: root_path },
  { name: "Everyday", url: category_path("everyday") },
  { name: "Character Counter" }
] %>

<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Character Counter</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Paste text to get a detailed breakdown of characters, letters, digits, special characters, lines, and words.</p>

    <%# Ad: leaderboard — placed below content heading per AdSense best practices %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <div data-controller="character-counter-calculator ad-engagement" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label for="character-counter-your-text" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Your Text</label>
            <textarea id="character-counter-your-text" data-character-counter-calculator-target="input" data-action="input->character-counter-calculator#calculate"
              class="w-full rounded-xl border-[1.5px] border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-600 bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 text-gray-900 dark:text-white p-3 text-sm font-mono focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500"
              rows="8" placeholder="Paste your text here..."></textarea>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-indigo-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Results</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Characters</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultCharacters">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Characters (no spaces)</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultCharactersNoSpaces">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Letters</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultLetters">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Digits</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultDigits">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Special Characters</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultSpecial">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Lines</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultLines">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Words</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-character-counter-calculator-target="resultWords">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->character-counter-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm shadow-blue-500/20 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-blue-500/25 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Results</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "character-counter" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Character Counter</h2>
      <p>
        Type or paste any text into the input field and the character counter immediately provides a comprehensive analysis. You see the total character count, character count excluding spaces, number of letters, digits, special characters, lines, and words. This is essential for checking text against platform limits, preparing content for social media, or analyzing the composition of any document.
      </p>
      <p>
        The character counter works entirely in your browser with no data sent to any server. Your text remains private and secure. It supports all languages and Unicode characters, making it suitable for content in any language including those with accented characters, Asian scripts, and emoji.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Why Character Counts Matter</h2>
      <p>
        Many platforms enforce strict character limits. Twitter allows 280 characters per tweet. Instagram captions max out at 2,200 characters. SMS messages split at 160 characters. Google shows approximately 155-160 characters of meta descriptions. LinkedIn posts perform best under 1,300 characters. Knowing your exact character count prevents truncation and ensures your message is delivered complete and intact.
      </p>

      <h3>Letters vs Characters</h3>
      <p>
        The distinction between letters and characters is important. Letters are alphabetic characters only, while the total character count includes everything: letters, digits, spaces, punctuation, and symbols. A password analyzer needs to know the composition of each type. A translator may charge by character count excluding spaces. An SEO specialist needs total character counts for meta tags. This tool gives you every breakdown you need in a single analysis.
      </p>

      <h3>Special Character Analysis</h3>
      <p>
        Special characters include punctuation marks, mathematical symbols, currency symbols, brackets, and other non-alphanumeric, non-whitespace characters. Understanding the special character density in your text helps with readability analysis, password strength assessment, and ensuring compatibility with systems that may not handle certain characters well. Emails, URLs, and code snippets typically have high special character counts.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>What is the difference between characters with and without spaces?</h3>
      <p>Characters with spaces counts everything. Characters without spaces excludes all whitespace. Some services charge per character excluding spaces.</p>

      <h3>What counts as a special character?</h3>
      <p>Any character that is not a letter, digit, or whitespace. This includes punctuation, symbols like @#$%, brackets, and mathematical operators.</p>

      <h3>Why does my count differ from Word?</h3>
      <p>Different tools handle whitespace differently. Windows line endings use two characters while Mac/Linux use one, which can cause discrepancies.</p>

      <h3>What character count should I target for SEO?</h3>
      <p>Title tags: under 60 characters. Meta descriptions: 155-160 characters. These limits ensure your text displays fully in search results.</p>

      <h3>Does it support Unicode?</h3>
      <p>Yes, fully. Accented letters, emoji, CJK characters, Arabic, Cyrillic, and all other Unicode are counted correctly.</p>

